 PEOPLES Democratic Party (PDP) in Delta State has fixed Saturday, August 8, for its congress. A statement by Publicity Secretary Ifeanyi Osuoza urged delegates to be law abiding. It reads: “The Delta State PDP has fixed Saturday, August 8, as the new date for its state congress. “Delegates are advised to comport themselves decently and maintain all COVID-19 guidelines and protocols during the exercise, including social distancing and regular washing of hands. All accredited delegates must come with their face masks, as there is a standing order of no face mask, no entry into the venue.”